| publisher = [[MTV News]]
| date = [[2007-02-15]]
| accessdate = 2007-02-15
}}</ref> and a telephone number that returns a clip of "Survivalism." Also found was the ''Year Zero'' song "My Violent Heart" from a [[thumb drive]] in a bathroom stall at a NIN show in Lisbon, Portugal. The fan participation in this [[alternate reality game]] has caught the attention of the media; [[MTV News]], ''[[USA Today]]'', and ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' have cited fansite The NIN Hotline, its forum Echoing the Sound, fan club The Spiral, and NinWiki as sources for new discoveries. Other leaked songs from the new album are: "Me, I'm Not" and "In This Twilight", both found in bathrooms at concerts during the [[European]] tour. This would suggest the band themselves are intentionally circulating the music to the public. In a concert in [[Spain]], Trent said that "the new album will probably be on the internet to steal in a couple of weeks." An unusual trailer is also available at the official website, along with the album cover.<ref name="MTVNews" /><ref>{{cite web
| url = http://blogs.usatoday.com/popcandy/2007/02/nins_web_of_int.html
